                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="18573" author="anno" created="Thu, 13 Jul 2006 05:39:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I found a better workaround than editing the tld inside the jar: Change the uri in springapp/war/WEB-INF/jsp/include.jsp by adding &quot;_rt&quot;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;%@ taglib prefix=&quot;c&quot; uri=&quot;http://java.sun.com/jstl/core_rt&quot; %&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="20709" author="anno" created="Thu, 9 Nov 2006 05:57:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;By now I learned enough to realize the real solution. When you upgrade web.xml to version 2.4 you must also change the namespace URI&apos;s in the taglib to conform with JSP 2.0. Specifically, you must insert jsp in the uri in include.jsp:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;%@ taglib prefix=&quot;c&quot; uri=&quot;http://java.sun.com/jsp/jstl/core&quot; %&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="21849" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Sun, 21 Jan 2007 03:30:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just noticed that Thomas fixed this for 2.0.1 already...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
